12. GPU register and memory lowering.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-register-lowering.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-register-lowering-band.fk` returns 511.
    - Scope: plain `fkwu --src` Form witness. It is GPU register/memory policy,
      not PTX/GLSL/MSL emission.
    - Proves: GPU register class, occupancy, shared memory, coalesced access,
      precision gate, fault map, source attribution, and parity receipt.

13. Deopt, melt, invalidation, and code cache.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-deopt-cache.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-deopt-cache-band.fk` returns 511.
    - Scope: plain `fkwu --src` Form witness. It is cache/deopt policy, not
      runtime dispatch.
    - Proves: install, keep, invalidate, attributed deopt, invalidation-to-rewalk,
      stale melt, fallback requirement, and source signature matching.

13a. Grouped JIT policy spine.
    - Status: landed in `observe/tests/jit-policy-front-sweep-band.fk`,
      `observe/tests/jit-policy-access-sweep-band.fk`, and
      `observe/tests/jit-policy-cache-sweep-band.fk`.
    - Witness: returns 31, 7, and 15 respectively.
    - Scope: grouped composed policy witness. Native emission/dispatch remains
      pending. One mega-concatenated sweep currently exceeds the `fkwu --src`
      256-symbol table and is not claimed.
    - Proves: profile receipts, runtime faults, tiering, inlining, static
      analysis, stack/frame, representation specialization, register lowering,
      and deopt/cache policies can coexist in one source-runner pass.

14. Compact Form-native emitter and guarded dispatch bundle.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-emitter-bundle.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-emitter-bundle-band.fk` returns 8191.
    - Scope: Form-native emitter/dispatch receipt model. It consumes the
      witnessed policy summaries without concatenating the entire policy spine,
      avoiding the current 256-symbol `--src` envelope.
    - Proves: complete policy receipts admit emission; emitted blocks carry
      guard, fallback, deopt-cache, runtime-fault-map, and source-map facts;
      guard-passing dispatch selects native; guard failure deopts to walker;
      runtime failure returns a source-attributed exception; invalidation rewalks;
      incomplete policy/source/fault maps block emission.

15. Form-native JIT IR lowering and interpreter.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-native-ir.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-native-ir-band.fk` returns 16383.
    - Scope: executable Form-owned IR lowering target and interpreter. It is not
      host machine code.
    - Proves: emitted programs carry source-attributed instructions; array
      lowering includes bounds checks; field lowering includes null checks; div
      lowering includes div-zero checks; guard-passing execution selects native;
      guard failure deopts to walker; runtime failure returns a source-attributed
      exception; invalidation rewalks; bad attribution is rejected; native/walker
      parity is witnessed for the passing sample.

16. Form-owned host dispatch packet and cache integration.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-host-dispatch.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-host-dispatch-band.fk` returns 8191.
    - Scope: Form-owned install/lookup/invalidate/execute contract over host
      dispatch packets. It is not host machine code execution.
    - Proves: CPU/GPU Form-IR packets install; foreign `c-lowering` packets are
      rejected; packets missing fault maps are rejected; matching valid packets
      hit the dispatch cache; signature mismatch and invalidation miss; cache
      hits execute through the Form IR interpreter; guard failure deopts; runtime
      failure returns a source-attributed exception; invalidated entries rewalk.

17. Form-owned backend emission bundle.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-backend-emission.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-backend-emission-band.fk` returns 8191.
    - Scope: backend emission metadata and execution simulation over compact
      dispatch packet summaries. It is not loaded host machine code.
    - Proves: x64, arm64, and PTX backend bundles are admitted from Form-owned
      packets; incompatible target emission is rejected; foreign `c-lowering`
      packets and backend owners are rejected; missing deopt metadata is
      rejected; code size follows lowered IR op count; guard/runtime passing
      execution selects native; guard failure deopts; runtime failure selects
      exception.

18. Form-owned backend byte/op stream emission.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-backend-bytes.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-backend-bytes-band.fk` returns 16383.
    - Scope: deterministic backend payload generation as Form data. It is not
      loaded or executed host machine code.
    - Proves: x64 byte payload, arm64 op-word payload, and PTX-like op-code
      payload emit only from Form-owned requests with source, guard, fault,
      deopt, root, and ABI maps; x64 payload has stable prologue, guard branch,
      and return bytes; arm64/PTX-like payloads have stable op streams; foreign
      `c-lowering`, missing deopt metadata, and missing source metadata reject.

19. Form-owned loader/executor contract.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-loader-contract.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-loader-contract-band.fk` returns 16383.
    - Scope: load/execute contract over Form-emitted payloads. It is not an
      `mmap`/W^X host primitive and not a function pointer call.
    - Proves: safe Form-owned payloads load into sealed executable non-writable
      slots; foreign `c-lowering`, missing deopt metadata, and missing source
      metadata reject; writable/unsealed slots are unsafe; guard/runtime/parity
      passing execution selects native; guard failure deopts; runtime failure
      returns an exception kind; invalidation rewalks; parity failure deopts.

19a. Merge checkpoint and existing runtime-door audit.
    - Status: landed in
      `receipts/2026-06-30-form-native-jit-merge-checkpoint.md`.
    - Witness: required bootstrap and every Form JIT band above passed on this
      checkout.
    - Scope: no C-seed changes. The existing `fk_native_call`,
      `fk_native_call_args`, and `fk_nat_install` host membrane is named as the
      already-present install/call door. The opt-in `FK_JIT=1` C
      proof-of-concept lowerer is explicitly not counted as this track's
      completion witness; on this Mac checkout it crystallized simple probes but
      returned `nothing`, so the next step must not depend on that C lowerer as
      truth.

19b. Form-owned native admission gate.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-native-admission.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-native-admission-band.fk` returns 131071.
    - Scope: executable Form admission chain; not host machine execution.
    - Proves: static analyzer success, Form-owned backend bytes, loader payload
      safety, sealed executable slot, native/deopt/exception/rewalk routing,
      walker fallback value, runtime exception kind, parity deopt, invalidation
      rewalk, and rejection of static div-zero source, foreign `c-lowering`,
      missing source maps, and unsafe generation-zero loads.

19c. Form-emitted carrier ABI byte bridge.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-carrier-abi.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-carrier-abi-band.fk` returns 32767 on this
      Mac checkout.
    - Scope: Form-emitted byte equivalence to the existing `native_call_test`
      payload and live carrier status classification. It is not a general
      arbitrary-byte source path into `fk_native_call`.
    - Proves: `model/form-asm-x64.fk` emits the exact Win64 and SysV `f(a)=a+1`
      carrier byte images, carries source/map metadata, rejects missing source
      metadata, keeps foreign `c-lowering` visible as foreign, and classifies
      the live host carrier as complete only if `native_call_test` returns
      `arg+1`. On this host the carrier returns `-1`, so completion remains
      pending rather than overclaimed.

19d. Backend emits carrier-compatible payloads.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-backend-carrier-payload.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-backend-carrier-payload-band.fk` returns 32767.
    - Scope: Form backend payload generation through the x64 encoder and loader
      action contract. It still does not pass arbitrary byte lists into
      `fk_native_call` at runtime.
    - Proves: Win64 and SysV carrier payload bytes are generated through
      `model/form-asm-x64.fk`, wrapped as safe backend byte outputs, admitted as
      safe loader payloads, loaded into safe slots, and routed through native,
      deopt, exception, rewalk, parity-deopt, and metadata-rejection paths.

19e. Form x64 checked-access payloads.
    - Status: landed in `observe/jit-checked-access-payload.fk`.
    - Witness: `observe/tests/jit-checked-access-payload-band.fk` returns
      2097151.
    - Scope: concrete Form-emitted x64 byte fragments for checked direct access.
      It still does not install or execute those byte lists through
      `fk_native_call`.
    - Proves: indexed array/list-slot loads carry null and bounds fault exits;
      field-slot loads carry null fault exits; signed division carries a
      div-by-zero fault exit; all three are admitted through the loader contract
      only with source, guard, fault, deopt, root, ABI, safepoint, and exception
